---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Carlos Jorques, an embedded control systems architect focused on physical systems, automotive software, diagnostics, and technical delivery."
>
	<section class="section">
		<div class="narrow">
			<SectionHeading
				eyebrow="About"
				title="Hi, I'm Carlos"
				description="I design and lead production-ready embedded control systems for vehicles and smart machines, connecting physical system intent with software, control logic, diagnostics, actuation, safety expectations, and delivery."
			/>
			<div class="prose">
				<h2>How I think</h2>
				<p>
					I start from intended system behavior: what the machine must sense, decide, protect,
					and do under real operating constraints. From there I work backward into interfaces,
					control logic, diagnostics, software responsibilities, verification needs, and delivery
					tradeoffs.
				</p>

				<h2>What I build</h2>
				<p>
					My work sits at the boundary between physical systems and embedded software:
					real-time control architecture, signal interpretation, diagnostic behavior, actuation
					logic, safety-related development, production reliability, and maintainable software
					integration.
				</p>

				<h2>From intent to execution</h2>
				<p>
					Good control systems are not only defined in models or requirements. They have to
					become production software that can be integrated, tested, optimized within safe
					boundaries, maintained by teams, and delivered under compliance, risk, supplier, and
					program constraints.
				</p>

				<h2>How I lead</h2>
				<p>
					I lead by making system behavior explicit, clarifying ownership boundaries, exposing
					tradeoffs early, and aligning software, controls, systems, diagnostics, safety,
					suppliers, and stakeholders around decisions that can survive implementation.
				</p>

				<h2>Research foundation</h2>
				<p>
					My PhD training supports rigorous thinking in modeling, analysis, and control. On
					this site, research is secondary evidence: it supports my industrial focus on embedded
					control architecture, reliable machine behavior, and production technical leadership.
				</p>

				<h2>Where I'm going</h2>
				<p>
					I am focused on control intelligence for physical systems: the engineering layer that
					helps smart machines sense, decide, protect themselves, and act reliably in the real
					world.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container about-grid">
			<div class="panel about-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Operating mode</p>
				<h2>Architecture, reliability, delivery</h2>
				<p>
					I connect real-time control architecture with production software integration,
					diagnostics, optimization boundaries, compliance awareness, and delivery execution.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="panel about-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Leadership focus</p>
				<h2>From technical intent to robust industrialization</h2>
				<p>
					I help teams move from concepts and requirements toward embedded control systems that
					can be integrated, verified, maintained, and trusted.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container">
			<ContactCTA />
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.about-card {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		padding: 1rem 0 0;
	}

	.about-card h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
	}

	@media (min-width: 760px) {
		.about-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		}
	}
</style>
